Boy OH Boy....things these past few days have been relatively interesting....mostly due to the fact that life is crazy...yes, it is crazy. One moment you could be extremely bored, the next, packed full of adventure and excitement...Therefore, i would love to examine a few parts of my life as of late and of later and of yet to come.

I'd like to call this Past, Present, and Future...An Analysis of

"Sometimes it is necessary to evaluate one's surroundings, to ponder one's life, and to reconsider all that one believes in."   -Matt E.

Wisely put my dear watson! Now, our little adventure will start this evening by exploring times....as of any confusing life, we'll visit the present first, then traveling to the past which ultimately should lead to expectations of the future. So bare with me as i recollect thoughts and eat my blueberries that i brought home from my workplace, Barb's.

The present to me consists of the day...yes, techniquely, it is the past, but its so close to mind, i want to refer to it as my present. At the present, i decided to clean my room. This was a task at hand. While cleaning, i decided to take it a step further and get rid of bad memories and things i can't stand to look at anymore. I then proceeded to the kitchen to grab a "tall kitchen bag" as i knew i would need it. I then proceeded to jam with blink 182 and clean like mad...throwing out random things that had no meaning what so ever and finding things that would go perfectly in my scrap book! memories can be so much fun!  So, about 2 "tall kitchen bags" later, i found a little blue box under my bed...this would happen to be the "ex-boyfriend box." Yes, i have one and no its not jam-packed on accounta i didn't expect things to be given to me from any of my boyfriends and i didn't ask for anything from my boyfriends.... ((entering the past)) but anyway, i began to look thru some of the things that were inside and the first few things i hit were from my elementary school crush...oh the good times!!! Brandon was such a sweetheart! I still have a card he made me for easter and something he bought me on our 5th grade field trip...lol! its so cute. Then i hit the next relationship with Mike Bloom. Oh those days were interesting...lol! I managed to save a card he got me for my bday that was so sweet, i couldn't throw it away and a picture of him in a dress...LMAO! oh the revenge i could have! But, Mike Bloom and i have set aside our past issues and do talk to each in a reasonable manner. Then, i hit the longest, most meaningful, and best ((yes i said best)) relationship yet...with ((Place random name here)). Oh, the stuff i managed to pile up in those pretty much 2 yrs. There were notes that he wrote him while in school, the tag from my HUGE carebear, OH and i even found this adorable thing he did...we were in history and the teach was talking about things ppl would do b/c thats what they believed and the one thing was writing a girl 3 love notes in order to marry her...and low and behold, thru out that day, i received 3 love notes...each one carefully numbered and sweetly put...lol! The days! Of course, not everything made it back into the box....a couple of shirts and odds and ends ended up in the "tall kitchen bag", but i kept the things that made me smile...for example the box my gummi bears came in that i got for easter! yay! lol! But as i was looking thru these things and as i read the empty promises made, i didn't get angry or upset or even sad...all i could do is smile at his attempts to sound sweet and make me smile. I'm guessing this is my sign saying "Ashlee, its okay to move on and you are ready to take on the world." I just couldn't believe how my reaction changed. Usually i get pissed and slam things away...but it was different...the last thing i looked at and am still debating on what to do with, was the xmas gift i got from him...it was the sweetest thing anyone has ever done for me...it was a collage of pictures of us and him and a poem he found that said everything so perfectly. Adorable.....Then, came the next two exboys....ugh...those relationships were complete downfalls. Josh and i did have some good moments, but...ya know, nothing special...there were a couple of movie stubs that i picked outta the box and put in the pile of things to go in my scrap book.....then came the last relationship....with christian....i managed to get a lot of shit while with him those almost 2 months, needless to say, nothing made it back to the box....totally not what i was looking for in a guy...he didn't have any rough edges....and i need rough edges! lol!

But now that i covered the past part of everything...lemme reflect on one thing i said about the sign saying, "Ashlee, its okay to move on and you are ready to take on the world"...this is what i would like to bring into the future part of my entry. I'm ready....i'm ready to see where each and every day will take me. Ready to try to have another relationship w/o looking at the past and comparing....i'm actually ready to forget...to forget the worst and move on with the best! Whos with me???? lol! Woot Woot!

This prolly doesn't make much sense to anyone out there, but hey, its my lj and i can talk about whatever the hell i want to.......or at least thats what frank told me! Speaking of Frank...he asked me to do him a flavor and write to lj and ask them to make him a girl goat that he can be friends with! I think i just may do so again...as i tried once...yes i did and i never got a responce...so i might as well try again! lol! I SHOULD prolly hit the hey on accounta i'm tired, but i have a few more thngs to do and then i'll be out!

So, until later my dearest friends ((and those that read this that are dumbwits and stupid idiots)) remember...mr. potatohead is the coolest potato around!

G'night!
